{"type":"message","id":"a86a6e0e","parentId":"f67cdf7f","timestamp":"2026-02-26T10:46:17.210Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"等搜索结果。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_37ba167ec5994420b5dd0d2a","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"nimble-bison","timeout":30000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":47431,"output":67,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47498,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772102774196}}
{"type":"message","id":"97d55af2","parentId":"a86a6e0e","timestamp":"2026-02-26T10:46:22.228Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_37ba167ec5994420b5dd0d2a","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"_heventure-search-mcp_ is a web search server that operates under the Model Context Protocol (MCP). This server allows users to perform searches without the need for an API key, simplifying the process of accessing web search capabilities. Specifically, it utilizes DuckDuckGo and Bing as its search engines, providing a user-friendly interface for retrieving search results.\n\nThe server supports asynchronous processing, which enhances performance during searches by allowing multiple requests to be handled simultaneously. This feature can significantly improve user experience, especially when conducting extensive searches or obtaining results in real-time. The functionality is ideal for developers and users alike who are looking to incorporate search capabilities into applications without the overhead of managing API keys or extensive configurations [1][3].\n\nFor those interested in the technical framework, heventure-search-mcp is part of a larger collection of MCP servers available on platforms such as mcpservers.org, which features a variety of servers dedicated to different search functionalities and categories. Users can explore these options to find solutions that best fit their requirements [2][10].\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"nimble-bison","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"_heventure-search-mcp_ is a web search server that operates under the Model Context Protocol (MCP). This server allows users to perform searches without the need for an API key, simplifying the process of accessing web search capabilities. Specifically, it utilizes DuckDuckGo and Bing as its search engines, providing a user-friendly interface for retrieving search results.\n\nThe server supports asynchronous processing, which enhances performance during searches by allowing multiple requests to be handled simultaneously. This feature can significantly improve user experience, especially when conducting extensive searches or obtaining results in real-time. The functionality is ideal for developers and users alike who are looking to incorporate search capabilities into applications without the overhead of managing API keys or extensive configurations [1][3].\n\nFor those interested in the technical framework, heventure-search-mcp is part of a larger collection of MCP servers available on platforms such as mcpservers.org, which features a variety of servers dedicated to different search functionalities and categories. Users can explore these options to find solutions that best fit their requirements [2][10].\n","name":"mcporter call"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772102782223}}
